John Jacob presents Shivan and Narresh at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week.

Shivan and Narresh’s Fresconian Series at the FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week was all about reimagining the visual splendor of Shekhawati Havelis in Rajasthan, painting to life India's opulent history and evolution through the modern lens of art and design. The contemporarisation of the mural musings and their new-age relevance in documenting and eternalizing the Shekhawati history and the lives of the people at that time enamors and inspires a modern canvas for the Fresconian Series. 5 prints were used in this collection which pay an ode to the artist as well as the artisans, exuding joy and creativity through poetic blends of shimmering skein luster and meticulous detailing. Hand-techniques such as hand knitting, crochet, hand-machine embroidery and shuttle needle-lace technique hero the intricacy of each garment.

latestPosts.caption:
NIF Global presents GenNext- That Antiquepiece at Lakmē Fashion Week in partnership with FDCI. 

That Antique Piece’s collection draws inspiration from archival photographs of the Rana queens of Nepal from the 1870s to the 1950s. With an abundance of resources and European influences, their imagination ran wild, resulting in breathtaking fashion and striking visual imagery in the foothills of the Himalayas. By extracting smaller elements from these historical references and reinterpreting their proportions, the collection explores braids, jewels, textiles, and volume—each representing a shared cultural heritage. These elements are then meticulously crafted into one-of-a-kind modern heirlooms, blending tradition with fine craftsmanship.

@nifglobal.corporate @that.antiquepiece @lakmeindia @fdciofficial @reliancebrandsltd @r1seworldwide

Abraham & Thakore at Lakmē Fashion Week in partnership with FDCI. 

Abraham & Thakore’s collection embraces serendipity, finding beauty in the forgotten and the everyday. Memories of obsolete or mundane objects are given a new vocabulary and contemporary context. This occasion-inspired evening wear collection recalls the past, presenting it in today’s fast-changing world while looking toward the future of fashion. The finest silks, georgettes, and organzas are combined with quirky materials, transforming them into ensembles of glamour and desire. The collection reimagines familiar items—from discarded sweet wrappers and brightly coloured plastic sheets to sacking materials and retro film or cassette tapes—creating bejewelled surfaces and intricate embroideries in a glamorous upcycling of almost-forgotten memorabilia.

@abrahamandthakore @lakmeindia @fdciofficial @nexaexperience @reliancebrandsltd @r1seworldwide

Revisiting LG MoodUP™️ Presents Gauri & Nainika from March 2024.

LG MoodUP™️ presents the Gauri & Nainika Fall Winter 2024 collection where every thread whispers tales of romance and sophistication. Inspired by the dazzling colours of LG’s innovative concept refrigerator, the collection features vivid colours, bold floral prints, oversized peony blooms, and intricate rose creeper patterns in a palette of deep pink, rich yellow, and soft pink. This year for fall, jewel tones in velvet take centre stage, adorned with meticulous crystal and pearl embroidery, transforming each garment into a dazzling canvas of elegance. Fabrics such as raw silk and duchess satin make a statement in voluminous gowns and tailored midi dresses, boasting vibrant shades of fuchsia and bottle green. Classic hues such as red, ivory, and black, beloved by the brand, also make an appearance in signature shapes on the runway. Intertwining with these statement-making pieces are easy silhouettes in crepe, including flowing shirt dresses and chiffon creations, adding an air of effortless grace to the line.

latestPosts.caption:
Revisiting Rajdeep Ranawat at Lakmē Fashion Week in partnership with FDCI. 

The magnificence of the Royal courtesans of Lucknow brings in the festive season with a dash of European elegance and a sprinkle of mid-18th century tapestry as the key inspiration for Rajdeep Ranawat’s collection, “Nizam”. A palette of pale seafoam, withered rose and pewter with the vibrance of mustard and garnet completes the collection with jewel tones of sapphire, ruby and tourmaline as accents throughout. 

@rajdeep.ranawat.official @lakmeindia @fdciofficial @nexaexperience @reliancebrandsltd @r1seworldwide 

#LakmēFashionWeekxFDCI #LFWxFDCI #LakmēFashionWeek #LFW #FDCI

Nothing X Amit Aggarwal at Lakmē Fashion Week in partnership with FDCI.

Amit Aggarwal is redefining the future of ready-to-wear with his new collection. With a continuing focus on easy to wear dressing, fashion intersects with heritage in new experiments with form & texture. The latest collection is all about versatility—clothing that is effortless, and made to be styled your way. Think wardrobe essentials with a statement edge—structured yet fluid silhouettes, easy layering pieces, and bold details that can be mixed and matched with anything, bringing together fashion & function in a seamless way. 

This season, classic tailoring meets unexpected draping, creating silhouettes that are as practical as they are fashion-forward. Cropped jackets, asymmetric hems, and lightweight separates redefine proportions while keeping comfort at the core. Whether you pair them with your favorite denim or luxe accessories, these pieces adapt to your personal style. 

@nothingindia @amitaggarwalofficial @lakmeindia @fdciofficial @reliancebrandsltd @r1seworldwide

latestPosts.caption:
La Martina X Rajesh Pratap Singh at at Lakmē Fashion Week in partnership with FDCI.

Set against the stunning backdrop of Mahalaxmi Racecourse, the showcase kicks off with a friendly polo match between the Guards Polo Club team and La Martina’s official team, graced by renowned players such as Phoebe Leake, Edward Morris Lowe, and Malcolm Borwick. Guards Polo Club, founded in 1955 by HRH The Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh, stands as one of the world’s top polo venues, with 600 games each season hosted in the heart of Windsor Great Park near Windsor Castle. The official La Martina polo team, representing India in the friendly match, boasts an impressive lineup featuring Navin Singh, Gaurav Sahgal, and Dino Dhankar, representing the spirit of polo heritage and excellence, and infusing the event with a thrilling fusion of fashion and sport.

OTT Tarun Tahiliani at Lakmē Fashion Week in partnership with FDCI. 

Tarun Tahiliani’s prêt label, OTT, debuts its second collection at Lakmē Fashion Week in partnership with FDCI, March 2025, blending Indian Modern aesthetics with modular separates. Hand-embroidered chikankari on linen and reimagined rabari craft add contemporary depth. Versatile silhouettes, including evening dresses and day jackets, feature vibrant artworks by the Singh Twins. A live presentation showcases the ease of mix-and-match styling, reflecting the modern Indian woman’s dynamic spirit.
